In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and almonds. Roll into 1-in. balls. Place 2 in. apart on greased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F for 9-11 minutes or until edges are firm. Remove to wire racks to cool.